Summary
  Can simulate a clickable link and render text at a specific angle.
Description
  To simulate a clickable link, do the following:
  
  * Set AutoOpenURL to true.
  * Set URL to a specific \URL or object, that will be opened when the user clicks the label.
  * Set HotTrack to true, and change HotTrackFont so the user gets feedback when the mouse passes
  over   the label.
  
  Use property Angle to display the label text at a specific angle.

