@@TJvCustomLabel.URL
Summary
  Specifies a URL associated with the label.
Description
  Use URL to associate a URL, an executable file, a document file, or a folder with the label. If
  AutoOpenURL is set to true and the user clicks on the label, then the object specified by URL is
  opened.
  
  You might want to adjust property HotTrackFont to visually simulate a clickable link.
  
  Some examples:
  <CODE>
  { Executable file }
  JvLabel1.URL := Application.ExeName;
  
  { Folder }
  JvLabel1.URL := ExtractFilePath(Application.ExeName); </CODE>
  Note
  If AutoOpenURL is set to false, then URL is ignored.

